      "id": "d6237660_42643a8b",
      "file_path": "policy-management/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/drools/system/PolicyEngineConstants.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 46,
      "message": "mark as \"volatile\".\n\nI think this may give sonars since it is currently unchangeable, I think it will reflect the inconsistency and suggest to be marked as final. I am not very keen on changing code just to satisfy tests.\n\nIf doing this, better to add a setter to make it easier for all unit tests in the future regardless.   You can mark with lombok @NonNull in the setter method, as should protect against week references.   So the other comment is to add a setter protecting against null values.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-30 15:24:08.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
